   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, William A. Huddard in Knoxville, Tenn. to his father in Ohio, 1864 April 8</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated April 8, 1864, William A. Huddard writes to his father in Ohio, giving him the news of his Division and discussing rumors that it will be moved from its current department to the "Department of the Cumberland." Also, he mentions that " there is to be but little done here in the way of a fight." He further informs his father that his regiment and the entire division are in good health and that he has "never seen the boys in better spirits."</abstract>
